---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { config } from "../config";
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service" description="Terms and conditions for using our products and services.">
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mb-8">Last updated: March 16, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">1. Agreement to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using the {config.companyName} website and products, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service.
          If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use our services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">2. Products and Services</h2>
        <p>
          {config.companyName} provides digital products including but not limited to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li>REST APIs and data services</li>
          <li>Automation workflow packages (n8n, etc.)</li>
          <li>Digital templates (PDF, spreadsheets)</li>
          <li>Claude Code skills and AI tools</li>
          <li>Web applications and SaaS tools</li>
          <li>Custom development services</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">3. Purchases and Payments</h2>
        <p>
          Payments are processed through third-party providers including Stripe, Gumroad, RapidAPI, Etsy, and Fiverr.
          Each platform's terms and refund policies apply in addition to these terms.
        </p>
        <p>
          All prices are listed in the currency specified on the respective platform. Prices may change without prior notice.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">4. Digital Product License</h2>
        <p>
          When you purchase a digital product (template, workflow pack, skill), you receive a
          <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">personal, non-transferable license</strong> to use the product
          for your own personal or business purposes. You may not:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li>Redistribute, resell, or share the product</li>
          <li>Claim the product as your own creation</li>
          <li>Use the product in a way that competes with {config.companyName}</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">5. API Usage</h2>
        <p>
          API access is subject to rate limits and fair use policies defined on RapidAPI or the relevant platform.
          Abuse, excessive requests, or attempts to circumvent rate limits may result in access being revoked.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">6. Refund Policy</h2>
        <p>
          Due to the digital nature of our products:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Digital downloads:</strong> No refunds after delivery, unless the product is materially defective.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">API subscriptions:</strong> Cancellable anytime through the platform. Pro-rated refunds per platform policy.</li>
          <li><strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Custom services:</strong> Refund terms defined per project agreement.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you believe a product is defective, contact us at <a href={`mailto:${config.email}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent-light)] hover:underline">{config.email}</a> within 14 days of purchase.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">7. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content, code, designs, and branding on this website and in our products are the property of {config.companyName}
          unless otherwise stated. Open-source components are used under their respective licenses.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          {config.companyName} provides products and services "as is" without warranty of any kind.
          We are not liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use of our products.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">9. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of the Republic of Estonia. Any disputes shall be resolved
          in the courts of Tallinn, Estonia.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">10. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date.
          Continued use of our services after changes constitutes acceptance.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">11. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms, contact:
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong class="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">{config.companyName}</strong><br />
          {config.location}<br />
          <a href={`mailto:${config.email}`} class="text-[var(--color-accent-light)] hover:underline">{config.email}</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
